.TH BUNPY-ADD 1 "2026-04-27" "bunpy" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bunpy-add \- add a single package to pyproject.toml and install it
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bunpy add
.I pkg
.RB [ <spec> ]
.RB [ --no-install ]
.RB [ --no-write ]
.RB [ --target
.IR dir ]
.RB [ --index
.IR url ]
.RB [ --cache-dir
.IR path ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Loads
.B ./pyproject.toml
in strict mode, fetches the project's PEP 691 page from the
configured simple index, picks the highest universal wheel
(\fBpy3-none-any\fR) that satisfies the caller's PEP 440 spec,
installs it through the
.BR bunpy-pm-install-wheel (1)
machinery, and writes the resolved spec back into
.BR [project].dependencies .
.PP
v0.1.3 is naive on purpose: there is no transitive walk, no
lockfile, and no resolver. Only universal wheels are considered;
platform wheels and the resolver land together in v0.1.5.
.PP
When the caller omits a spec, the line written into
.B [project].dependencies
is
.IR name >= resolved-version .
When the caller provides a spec, it is written verbatim. Re-adding
an already-listed package replaces its line with the new spec.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --no-install
Update the manifest only; do not download or install.
.TP
.B --no-write
Install only; do not modify
.BR pyproject.toml .
.TP
.BI --target " dir"
site-packages target. Default
.BR ./.bunpy/site-packages .
.TP
.BI --index " url"
Override the simple index URL.
.TP
.BI --cache-dir " path"
Override the cache root.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B BUNPY_PYPI_FIXTURES
When set, redirects index and wheel fetches to a fixture root.
Test-only.
.TP
.B BUNPY_CACHE_DIR
Overrides the cache root used for index responses and wheel
bodies.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Zero on a successful add. Non-zero on a manifest error, an
unsatisfied spec, a fetch failure, an unsafe wheel, or an I/O
failure.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bunpy-pm-install-wheel (1),
.BR bunpy-pm-info (1),
.BR bunpy-pm-config (1),
.BR bunpy (1).
